column10:
The fact that this game is made by Ubisoft is unbelieveable . Because it is......."Good" it was made with love and dedication which is not a thing in Ubisoft for quite a while . So I gave it a decent 9/10 

{ Graphics } 

+ San Francisco appears as a beautiful city, everything from the buildings, the lighting, the environment , the npc is just so spectacular, hard to believe this game came out in 2016 
+ The characters model is good and detail, but normal NPC model is not up to par

{ Gameplay }

+ Now this is where Watch Dog 2 really shines. The gameplay expanded a lot compared to the first game, It nails the hacking system very well with a variety of options like: phone distraction, vehicle control, traffic control, security system shutdown, robot hacking and of course, one of the best things they ever add and ever exist in a video game is planting fault evident which make the police or the gang to attack someone . You too lazy to learn the enemeis location to sneak in their base ? just call an entire SWAT team on them and they gonna create enough distraction for you to go in 
+ I have to give the parkour system big credit for making the game movement so smooth and enjoyable . There are also variety of parkour animation , my favourite is back flip and front flip 
+ Gun play is so so , i don't have much to say about it 

{ Story } 

+ The story is decent , not great but decent . The thing that stands out for me the most is not the actual story itself, but the interesting characters that we meet , i mean by that is my gang : Wrench, Josh , Horatio , Sitara and the main character himself Marcus  . Their personality is quite unique and the way Ubisoft show them is Amazing 
+ Wrench with his iconic mask. He is so fun to talk to , he is hilarious always make jokes throughout the adventure, he like destroying stuff . My man having a serious problem with animal though XD
+ Josh is like a depressed kid . He is quiet ,doesn't talk much kinda socially awkward but very smart. That doesn't mean he is boring , he brings a different sort of humor to the game like when he try to find out what "cornhole" mean XD
+ Sitara is the only woman in the team , my girl is a real artist and DJ , very talented . She is the face of dedsec cause without her drawing skills dedsec have no appearance
+ Horatio is kinda bland because Ubisoft some how doesn't  give him much screen time. He is nice and vibe dude 

{ Audio } 

+ Voice actiong is great
+ Music is...... so so , i don't find myself listen much to the music in game. But it is cool that you allow to pick a song to listen to all the time even in combat 

{ Difficulty } 

+ Gun play is balance , our health is not superior than our enemies like other game . We die like after 4 to 5 shoot and believe me ,you gonna die a lot if not careful
+ Enemies AI is Smart . They don't just take cover and shoot back, they actually have strategy like some guys in the front keep you busy while the others rotate and try to flank you, and since you die after 4 to 5 shoot like i said, direct combat is not recommend
+ Well.....Here is reason why the game is not 10/10 . It the stealth system , WHAT KIND OF GAME where one enemies spot you even just for 0.1s after you take him down, the entire army knew exactly where you are and jump on you. 

{ PC requirement } 

+ You need a decent laptop/pc to run this game 

{ Game time } 

+ pretty long ( 17h-30h )

{ Bugs } 

+ i don't see any bug 

{ Final thought } 

+ There are still a ton of thing i haven't talk about like normal NPC AI , dialogue , Car physics, hacking puzzle, side quest and stuff.....
But This game is good and for me it is the best game Ubisoft ever create
